thread.title: CHS girls golf ends season at A-J Regional
thread.title_full: CHS girls golf ends season at A-J Regional

author: Jim Beers Reporter
title: CHS girls golf ends season at A-J Regional
text: Randolph County Herald Tribune - Chester, IL By Jim Beers Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:45 AM By Jim BeersReporter Posted Oct. 8, 2015 at 10:45 AM A much-improved Lady Yellow Jackets golf team competed in the Class A Anna-Jonesboro Regional on Wednesday and in spite of a great effort, no Chester athletes qualified for sectional competition. Massac County won the match with a low score of just 350 strokes, while Herrin (367); Carterville (368), Anna-Jonesboro (378) and Murphysboro (408) rounded out the top five. “The Lady Jackets never laid down,” said CHS assistant coach Paul Zemlyn. “They came to fight and this time they gave it their all. “I will say that the girls were there every day for practice, worked hard and never quit.” The top three teams and 10 individuals advanced to the Carterville Sectional on Monday.the top 10 individuals advancing were Alexia Burtis of Harrisburg (87); Grace Coleman of Trico (91); Tanner Stadelbacher of Anna-Jonesboro (92); Meghan Smith of Anna-Jonesboro (92); Cassandra Jones of Goreville (94); Sydney Ray of Anna-Jonesboro (96); Hannah Gahagan of Murphysboro (96); Connar Hadley of Anna-Jonesboro (98); Skylar Street of Harrisburg (99) and Hailley Abernathy of Anna-Jonesboro (100). The Lady Yellow Jackets were led by juniors Emily Tudor and Jackie Hopkins, who both shot 113. Hanna Bert, a rookie sophomore golfer for the Lady Yellow Jackets, carded a 131 and senior Sarah Hecht finished with a 142. “I’m so proud of our girls,” Zemlyn said. “We coaches found that the girls got better as the season progressed and I really want to wish them good luck down the road. “We will really miss our three senior girls; Sarah Hecht, Jaclyn Colvis and Anna Cole.” By Jim Beers Randolph County Herald Tribune - Chester, IL By Jim Beers
